      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "Scorecard cleanup pass for 0.3.5\n\n- Replace bare `document` references with `activeDocument` and bare\n  `setTimeout`/`clearTimeout` with the `window.*` forms for\n  popout-window compatibility; swap `document.createElement` /\n  `createElementNS` / `createEl('span')` for the Obsidian\n  `createDiv` / `createSpan` / `createSvg` helpers; use\n  `.instanceOf(...)` instead of `instanceof` for cross-window\n  checks. Most autofixed by obsidianmd 0.3.0.\n- `console.info` migration messages downgraded to `console.debug`\n  (only warn/error/debug are allowed).\n- editor-paste / editor-drop handlers: add the genuine\n  `evt.defaultPrevented` early-return guard. preventDefault is\n  already called conditionally inside PasteHandler only when an image\n  is actually handled, so the obsidianmd/editor-drop-paste heuristic\n  (which can't see across the delegate) is suppressed with a precise\n  rationale rather than calling preventDefault unconditionally, which\n  would swallow normal text paste / drag-and-drop.\n- Type the nested-property walker in mdx-frontmatter.ts so indexing is\n  guarded by a runtime object check instead of implicit any.\n- Reword UI strings flagged by obsidianmd/ui/sentence-case (which can't\n  be disabled): brand-name and URL descriptions rephrased to clean\n  sentence case or naturally path-skippable forms, placeholders\n  capitalized. No behavioral change.\n- styles.css: merge the duplicate `.image-inserter-container\n  .container` block, drop the dead non-Chromium `background`\n  fallback (Obsidian is Chromium so the -webkit- value always wins),\n  and remove four override flags on the static-banner rules by raising\n  selector specificity with the doubled-class trick.\n- Add `pnpm.overrides` for the minimatch / picomatch /\n  brace-expansion / ajv / flatted / yaml chain, upgrade\n  eslint-plugin-obsidianmd 0.1.9 -> 0.3.0 scoped to TypeScript, drop\n  the broken preinstall script, and move `obsidian` from a\n  `\"latest\"` runtime dependency to a pinned devDependency.\n- Gate the esbuild sourcemap on build mode: production ships\n  `sourcemap: false` so the release main.js is byte-reproducible and\n  passes build verification; dev/watch keeps the inline sourcemap.\n- Add a portable CONTRIBUTING.md and the canonical release workflow\n  (manifest-version read, build provenance attestation, commit-message\n  release notes, workflow_dispatch recovery).\n\nBump to 0.3.5.\n\n---\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/davidvkimball/obsidian-image-manager/compare/0.3.4...0.3.5",
